{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5c7546c9-7ad1-4304-b50b-2fe3827b6f63","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload).\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — run only tests whose name contains that string. The `~` operator means \"contains\".\n\nYou can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d3b673ca-a2e0-44a6-9a02-09befe898662","outputTokens":157,"requestId":"A803:2B8468:667AE12:6EF1C2C:6A034C16"},"id":"c18a5d0f-049d-45b2-832d-e1192fe48029","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:49:52.058Z","parentId":"03225596-2765-4136-8ac0-bb1d55ceac25"}
